As Opposition Parties In Ethiopia Embrace Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed’s Concept Of Coming Together To Form A United Prosperous Party, The OGADEN National Liberation Front Have Rejected To The Idea. The Latest Party To Join The Prosperity Party Was Somali Democratic Party, A Significant Gain In His Attempt To Form The New Party. Our Reporter Ali Manzu, Had A One On One With Olf Chairman Dr. Abdulrahman Mahad, And Sheds More Light On His Trip To Kenya And Why They Feel Safe As An Opposition Political Party In Ethiopia.